<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q8_v9" title="Q8_v9" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Registro del caso:</p>
    <p>Se prepararán vasos de jugo de naranja para un evento deportivo. En la siguiente tabla se muestra la cantidad de cada ingrediente que lleva un vaso.</p>
    <table border="1">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Ingrediente</th>
          <th>Cantidad por vaso (onzas)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Jugo de naranja</td>
          <td>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo> </m:mo>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            onzas
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Agua mineral</td>
          <td>
            <m:math>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:math>
            onzas
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Se prepararán 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>160</m:mn>
      </m:math>
      vasos y se considera que
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        <m:mo> </m:mo>
        <m:mi>onza</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mn>30</m:mn>
        <m:mo> </m:mo>
        <m:mi>mL</m:mi>
      </m:math>.
    </p>
    <p>¿Cuál de las siguientes cantidades totales de jugo de naranja, en mL, es coherente con la información de la tabla?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>Según el registro, ¿qué cantidad mantiene correctamente la razón indicada?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">45 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Cada vaso lleva <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math> onzas de jugo de naranja. Para <m:math><m:mn>160</m:mn></m:math> vasos, el total es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> onzas. Luego, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>240</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> mL. Por lo tanto, 45 mL no es coherente con la tabla.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">7200 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Cada vaso lleva <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math> onzas de jugo de naranja, es decir, <m:math><m:mn>1,5</m:mn></m:math> onzas. Para <m:math><m:mn>160</m:mn></m:math> vasos, se necesitan <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> onzas. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>onza</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mi>mL</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>240</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> mL.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">240 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al multiplicar la cantidad de jugo por vaso por los <m:math><m:mn>160</m:mn></m:math> vasos se obtiene <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, pero ese resultado está en onzas, no en mL. Al convertir, resulta <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>240</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> mL. Por lo tanto, 240 mL no es coherente con la información dada.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">16800 mL<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La pregunta pide solo el jugo de naranja. Ese ingrediente corresponde a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> onzas, que equivalen a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>240</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> mL. El valor <m:math><m:mn>16&#160;800</m:mn></m:math> mL se obtiene al sumar ambos ingredientes por vaso, porque <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3,5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> onzas por vaso, luego <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>560</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> onzas y <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>560</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>16&#160;800</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> mL.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la cantidad de jugo de naranja por vaso</strong></p>
            <p>La tabla indica que cada vaso lleva <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math> onzas de jugo de naranja.</p>
            <p>Eso equivale a <m:math><m:mn>1,5</m:mn></m:math> onzas por vaso.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular la cantidad total de jugo de naranja en onzas</strong></p>
            <p>Como se prepararán <m:math><m:mn>160</m:mn></m:math> vasos, multiplicamos:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>En total se necesitan <m:math><m:mn>240</m:mn></m:math> onzas de jugo de naranja.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir onzas a mililitros</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado indica que <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>onza</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mi>mL</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>240</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
            <p>La cantidad total es <m:math><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:math> mL.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La única opción que coincide con <m:math><m:mn>7&#160;200</m:mn></m:math> mL es la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La cantidad total de jugo de naranja coherente con la tabla es <strong>7 200 mL</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>